"title": "5335: herald",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5335: herald",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>One who proclaims a message or paves the way for a promised event. In Scripture both angels and human beings are employed as heralds, and on occasions even specific events may herald future happenings.</p>\n<h2>Heralds in human affairs</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:28\">2KI 18:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod5:10\">EXO 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:7\">1SA 11:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:19\">2SA 18:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:12\">1KI 21:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:20\">2KI 10:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:12\">2KI 11:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:6\">2CH 30:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:19-Esth1:22\">EST 1:19–1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth6:11\">EST 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:4\">DAN 3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:7\">JON 3:7</a></p>\n<h2>To preach is to act as a herald</h2>\n<h3>Pronouncing judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:4\">JON 3:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:5\">JER 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:14\">JER 46:14</a></p>\n<h3>Bringing good news</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:9\">ISA 40:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:20\">ISA 48:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:7-Isa52:8\">ISA 52:7–52:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:15\">NAM 1:15</a></p>\n<h3>Preaching the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:14\">MAT 24:14</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:42\">ACT 5:42</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:7\">1TI 2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:2\">ACT 4:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:5\">ACT 8:5</a> <em>Philip proclaims the gospel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:20\">ACT 9:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:42\">ACT 10:42</a> <em>Peter at Cornelius' house</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:7\">ACT 15:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:3\">ACT 17:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:31\">ACT 28:31</a> <em>Paul preaches at Rome</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:23\">1CO 1:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:19\">2CO 1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:2\">GAL 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:23\">COL 1:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:16\">1TI 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:11\">2TI 1:11</a></p>\n<h2>John the Baptist as a herald</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:10\">MAT 11:10</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:2\">MRK 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:27\">LUK 7:27</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:1\">MAL 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:1-Matt3:3\">MAT 3:1–3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:3\">ISA 40:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:17\">LUK 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:76\">LUK 1:76</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:15\">JHN 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:28\">JHN 3:28</a></p>\n<h2>Angels as heralds</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:10\">LUK 2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:12\">JDG 6:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:20-Matt1:21\">MAT 1:20–1:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:5-Matt28:6\">MAT 28:5–28:6</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:5-Mark16:6\">MRK 16:5–16:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:4-Luke24:6\">LUK 24:4–24:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:13\">LUK 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:30-Luke1:31\">LUK 1:30–1:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:13-Luke2:14\">LUK 2:13–2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:6\">REV 14:6</a></p>\n<h2>Events heralding what is to happen</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:32-Matt24:33\">MAT 24:32–24:33</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:28-Mark13:29\">MRK 13:28–13:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:29-Luke21:31\">LUK 21:29–21:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:3\">2TH 2:3</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as a herald</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:43\">LUK 4:43</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:38\">MRK 1:38</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:17\">MAT 4:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:14-Mark1:15\">MRK 1:14–1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:18-Luke4:19\">LUK 4:18–4:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1-Isa61:2\">ISA 61:1–61:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:1\">LUK 8:1</a></p>",
